simulate /ˈsɪmjʊleɪt/

(simulating,simulated,simulates) 

1. V-T If you simulate an action or a feeling, you pretend that you are doing it or feeling it. 假装 

例： They rolled about on the Gilligan Road, simulating a bloodthirsty fight. 他们在吉利根路上打滚，模拟一场血腥的战斗。 

2. V-T If you simulate a set of conditions, you create them artificially, for example, in order to conduct an experiment. 模拟 

例： The scientist developed one model to simulate a full year of the globe's climate. 这位科学家研制出一个模型，能模拟全年地球的气候。

